result.name: Gyu Gin

reviews.text:
Not bad, numerous of vegetables you can choose, with their signature beef cuffy, which is very delicious and branded ice cream.  Love it.
Of course they mainly sell sliced fatty beef and pork, which divides into different grades as a set and they will offwr you free flow of drinks if you ordered set of more than $199, if you live non stop drinking beer, must choose that set then.
Small restaurant located just right by Langham MTR, very easy to find. I went for $199 all you can eat 1.5 hours , the beef was good and the service was nice.
Good price (the cheapest set)

Loving the all you can eat style for the hotpot. For me, I'm not a huge meat fan so, the lunch deals are perfect cause we get only one box of beef per person and I can stock on a lot of the vegetables and mushrooms and fish balls! The best part is the haagen dazs ice cream you can eat while you're there. There's usually a time limit depending on which price you choose. For example, during lunch time the time limit ranges from an hour to 90 minutes

So so. Food was ok. Soup base not that good. Beef was decent. Went for the $300 option beef but not that great and not worth the extra money. Maybe $200 is decent enough. Free flow drinks and Asahi and Haagen Dazs was good and makes it decent value. 90 mins eating time is quite short and annoying that they are quite strict even though restaurant had empty seats and we had stop eating by then.

result.name: 牛陣

reviews.text: 日式邊爐🔥

服務比上次
至少冇話一夠鐘就攞走個鍋
服務態度好， 食物品質有待改善， 基本上食材比較普通， 個雪糕特別好食。
員工勁有禮貌，食物質素進步了不少！
仍維持幾年前差不多的服務與質素，沒有大進步也沒有大退步
